(228, '_transient_ti_about_plugin_info_wp-maintenance-mode', 'O:8:\"stdClass\":26:{s:4:\"name\";s:73:\"LightStart &#8211; Maintenance Mode, Coming Soon and Landing Page Builder\";s:4:\"slug\";s:19:\"wp-maintenance-mode\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"2.6.9\";s:6:\"author\";s:46:\"<a href=\"https://themeisle.com/\">Themeisle</a>\";s:14:\"author_profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/themeisle/\";s:12:\"contributors\";a:1:{s:9:\"themeisle\";a:3:{s:7:\"profile\";s:41:\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/themeisle/\";s:6:\"avatar\";s:88:\"https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a0ec097eaf5f30933eb00c1175d4bd55?s=96&d=monsterid&r=g\";s:12:\"display_name\";s:9:\"Themeisle\";}}s:12:\"requires_php\";s:3:\"5.6\";s:16:\"requires_plugins\";a:0:{}s:7:\"ratings\";a:5:{i:5;i:623;i:4;i:35;i:3;i:28;i:2;i:16;i:1;i:98;}s:11:\"num_ratings\";i:800;s:11:\"support_url\";s:57:\"https://wordpress.org/support/plugin/wp-maintenance-mode/\";s:15:\"support_threads\";i:1;s:24:\"support_threads_resolved\";i:1;s:15:\"active_installs\";i:700000;s:8:\"homepage\";s:0:\"\";s:8:\"sections\";a:6:{s:11:\"description\";s:2944:\"<p>Add a maintenance page to your blog that lets visitors know your blog is down for maintenance, add a coming soon page for a new website or create a landing page for an existing site. User with admin rights gets full access to the blog including the front end.</p>\n<p>Activate the plugin and your blog is in maintenance-mode, works and only registered users with enough rights can see the front end. You can use a date with a countdown timer for visitor information or set a value and unit for information.</p>\n<p>Also works with WordPress Multisite installs (each blog from the network has its own maintenance settings).</p>\n<h4>FunzionalitÃ </h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fully customizable (change colors, texts and backgrounds).</li>\n<li>Subscription form (export emails to .csv file).</li>\n<li>Countdown timer (remaining time).</li>\n<li>Contact form (receive emails from visitors).</li>\n<li>Coming soon page;</li>\n<li>Landing page templates;</li>\n<li>WordPress multisite;</li>\n<li>Responsive design;</li>\n<li>Social media icons;</li>\n<li>Works with any WordPress theme;</li>\n<li>SEO options;</li>\n<li>Exclude URLs from maintenance;</li>\n<li>Bot functionality to collect the emails in a friendly and efficient way;</li>\n<li>GDPR Ready;</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Bugs, technical hints or contribute</h4>\n<p>Please give us feedback, contribute and file technical bugs on <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">GitHub Repo</a>.</p>\n<h4>Riconoscimenti</h4>\n<p>Developed by <a href=\"https://themeisle.com\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Themeisle</a></p>\n<h4>What&#8217;s Next</h4>\n<p>If you like this plugin, then consider checking out our other projects:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://optimole.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Optimole</a> &#8211; Optimole is your all-in-one image optimization solution for WordPress &amp; beyond.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpshout.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WPShout</a> &#8211; In-Depth WordPress Tutorials for Developers</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://revive.social/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Revive Social</a> &#8211; Revive Old Posts helps you keep your content alive and in front the audiences that matter.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.codeinwp.com/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">CodeinWP</a> &#8211; CodeinWP stands for all-things-WordPress. From web design to freelancing and from development to business, your questions are covered.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://domainwheel.com\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">DomainWheel</a> &#8211; Free Short Website name generator, with the help of AI, for instant ideas.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Check-out <a href=\"https://themeisle.com/blog/\" title=\"Themeisle blog\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">our blog</a> to learn from our <a href=\"https://themeisle.com/blog/category/wordpress/reviews/\" title=\"WordPress Reviews\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WordPress Reviews</a> and see other <a href=\"https://themeisle.com/blog/category/wordpress-plugins/\" title=\"WordPress Plugins Comparisons\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">WordPress plugins</a>.</p>\n\";s:12:\"installation\";s:362:\"<ol>\n<li>Unpack the download package</li>\n<li>Upload all files to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory, include folders</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Go to <code>Settings</code> page, where you can change what settings you need (pay attention to <strong>Exclude</strong> option!)</li>\n</ol>\n\";s:3:\"faq\";s:834:\"\n<dt id=\'how%20to%20use%20plugin%20filters\'>\nHow to use plugin filters\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>Check out our <a href=\"https://github.com/codeinwp/Snippet-Library/\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Snippet Library</a>.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\'cache%20plugin%20support\'>\nCache Plugin Support\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>WP Maintenance Mode can be unstable due to the cache plugins; we recommend deactivating any cache plugin when maintenance mode is active. If you <strong>really</strong> want to use a cache plugin, make sure you delete the entire cache after each change.</p>\n</p>\n<dt id=\'exclude%20list\'>\nExclude list\n</h4>\n<p>\n<p>If you change your login url, please add the new slug (url: http://domain.com/newlogin, then you should add: newlogin) to Exclude list from plugin settings -&gt; General Tab.</p>\n<p>Notice: <code>wp-cron.php</code> is excluded by default.</p>\n</p>\n\n\";s:9:\"changelog\";s:9562:\"<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.8...v2.6.9\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.9</a> (2023-12-22)</p>\n<h3>Bug Fixes</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed compatibility issue with WP 6.4</li>\n<li>Fixed broken templates layout issue on the Safari browser</li>\n<li>Enhanced security</li>\n<li>Fixed compatibility issue with WP-Optimize</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.7...v2.6.8\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.8</a> (2023-06-07)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix the Save button Module tab not working</li>\n<li>Codebase updates</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.6...v2.6.7\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.7</a> (2023-04-01)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bug fix: Addressed an unnecessary &#8216;no maintenance page&#8217; error occurrence.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.5...v2.6.6\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.6</a> (2023-03-31)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Remove error notice for users that use an overriding custom template</li>\n<li>Update dependencies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.4...v2.6.5\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.5</a> (2023-03-01)</p>\n<p>Update dependencies</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.3...v2.6.4\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.4</a> (2023-02-24)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add the option to manage maintenance status on all sites from the network dashboard</li>\n<li>Update dependencies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.2...v2.6.3\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.3</a> (2023-02-06)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Update dependencies</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.1...v2.6.2\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.2</a> (2022-12-16)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add the option in the wizard to skip importing a template and installing Otter</li>\n<li>Improve the quality of the template screenshots</li>\n<li>Fix the template overriding issue</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.6.0...v2.6.1\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.1</a> (2022-11-03)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Add a notice to announce the rebrand of the plugin</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.5.4...v2.6.0\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.6.0</a> (2022-11-02)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Adds Landing pages templates</li>\n<li>Adds more Coming soon and Maintenance mode templates</li>\n<li>Rebrand the plugin into LightStart</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.5.3...v2.5.4\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.5.4</a> (2022-10-10)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix subscribers entry export for legacy forms.</li>\n<li>Fix PHP notice showing up on edge cases new installs.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.5.2...v2.5.3\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.5.3</a> (2022-09-28)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix wrong template loaded when the current post template is empty.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.5.1...v2.5.2\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.5.2</a> (2022-09-27)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix maintenance mode issue for previously logged users <a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/issues/321\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#321</a></li>\n<li>Allow comments into exclude textarea so that you can comment on the IP addresses for location, props <a href=\"https://github.com/joostdekeijzer\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">@joostdekeijzer</a></li>\n<li>Fix PHP notice errors on specific scenarios <a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/issues/324\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#324</a></li>\n<li>Fix Otter for saving subscriber entry</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.5.0...v2.5.1\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.5.1</a> (2022-09-08)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixes a bug which was causing error on some instances</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.7...v2.5.0\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.5.0</a> (2022-09-08)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>New Feature: Adds compatibility with Block Editor or any page builder for building the maintenance mode page.</li>\n<li>New Feature: Adds coming soon and maintenance mode starting templates.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.6...v2.4.7\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.4.7</a> (2022-08-08)</p>\n<p>Fixes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fix login form display</li>\n<li>Fix email collecting by the bot</li>\n<li>Improve accessibility of the maintenance page thanks to @SophieWeb</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.5...v2.4.6\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.4.6</a> (2022-06-15)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Improve data sanitizations for custom css and contact module</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.4...v2.4.5\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.4.5</a> (2022-06-15)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Harden security and improve release process</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.3...v2.4.4\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.4.4</a> (2022-02-10)</p>\n<p>Update dependencies</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/Codeinwp/wp-maintenance-mode/compare/v2.4.2...v2.4.3\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">Version 2.4.3</a> (2022-01-27)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Change ownership to Themeisle</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.4.2 (18/01/2022)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Misc: 900 000 Active Installs Celebrations!</li>\n<li>Misc: WordPress 5.9 compatibility</li>\n<li>Fix: jQuery UI CSS theme reference from jQuery CDN</li>\n<li>Misc: Text fixes in the dashboard</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.4.1 (20/07/2021)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Misc: WordPress 5.8 compatibility</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.4.0 (13/05/2021)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Design: add &#8220;Custom CSS&#8221; setting; Finally! ð</li>\n<li>Design: add &#8220;Footer links&#8221; color setting</li>\n<li>Design: add a list of available shortcodes under the &#8220;Text&#8221; editor</li>\n<li>Bot: make {visitor_name} placeholder work in all messages after the visitor types his name</li>\n<li>Misc: add [embed] shortcode for responsive video embeds; Compatible with YouTube, Vimeo, DailyMotion.</li>\n<li>Misc: make the exclude mechanism work with Cyrillic characters</li>\n<li>Misc: add <code>wpmm_maintenance_template</code> filter; It works the same way as the <code>wpmm_contact_template</code> filter, but for the maintenance template.</li>\n<li>Misc: now you can override the <code>contact</code> email template too; Check <code>/views/contact.php</code> for more details.</li>\n<li>Misc: better compatibility with translation plugins like Loco Translate</li>\n<li>Misc: the image uploaders (from the dashboard) are now translatable</li>\n<li>Misc: improve uninstall routine</li>\n<li>Misc: add <code>wpmm_delete_cache</code> action; It is called after each setting change.</li>\n<li>Misc: add support for cache plugins like WP Rocket, WP Fastest Cache, Endurance Page Cache, Swift Performance Lite, Cache Enabler, SG Optimizer, LiteSpeed Cache, Nginx Helper;</li>\n<li>Misc: remove <code>wpmm_count_where</code> helper function</li>\n<li>Misc: code improvements</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.3.0 (07/12/2020)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Modules: add support for Google Analytics 4 measurement ID</li>\n<li>Design: enable media buttons on wp_editor (now you can add images from the editor)</li>\n<li>Bot: fix translation issue</li>\n<li>Misc: add filters for capabilities <code>wpmm_settings_capability</code>, <code>wpmm_subscribers_capability</code>, and <code>wpmm_all_actions_capability</code> (the last one can be used to override all capabilities)</li>\n<li>Misc: fix [loginform] shortcode redirect attribute</li>\n<li>Misc: a few CSS &amp; Javascript improvements</li>\n<li>Misc: bump &#8220;Tested up to&#8221; version to 5.6</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.2.4 (20/05/2019)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>bump &#8220;Tested up to&#8221; to 5.2.0</li>\n<li>fix typo in Italian translation (it_IT)</li>\n<li>Bot: add a note about how you can export the list of subscribers <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode/issues/195\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#195</a></li>\n<li>Bot: add client-side sanitization to the input fields <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode/issues/176\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#176</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.2.3 (20/02/2019)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>bump &#8220;Tested up to&#8221; version to 5.1.0</li>\n<li>replace &#8220;wpmu_new_blog&#8221; action with &#8220;wp_initialize_site&#8221; action for WP 5.1.0 users because the first one is deprecated in the new version</li>\n<li>small improvement to &#8220;check_exclude&#8221; method from &#8220;WP_Maintenance_Mode&#8221; class</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.2.2 (27/11/2018)</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Google Analytics module: migrate from analytics.js to gtag.js + add ip anonymization <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode/issues/178\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#178</a></li>\n<li>GDPR module: accept links inside texareas + add policy link target <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode/issues/188\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#188</a></li>\n<li>add charset meta tag <a href=\"https://github.com/andrianvaleanu/WP-Maintenance-Mode/issues/200\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">#200</a></li>\n<li>fix PHP Notice:  Undefined index: HTTP_USER_AGENT</li>\n<li>add plural and single form translation for subscribers number (settings page)</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>Earlier versions</h4>\n<p>For the changelog of earlier versions, please refer to the <a href=\"https://plugins.svn.wordpress.org/wp-maintenance-mode/trunk/changelog.txt\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">full changelog</a>.</p>\n\";s:11:\"screenshots\";s:1679:\"<ol><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=976658\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=976658\" alt=\"Maintenance Mode Example\"></a><p>Maintenance Mode Example</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=976658\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=976658\" alt=\"Maintenance Mode Example #2\"></a><p>Maintenance Mode Example #2</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1834233\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1834233\" alt=\"Bot Example\"></a><p>Bot Example</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=976658\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=976658\" alt=\"Dashboard General Settings\"></a><p>Dashboard General Settings</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=976658\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=976658\" alt=\"Dashboard Design Settings\"></a><p>Dashboard Design Settings</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=976658\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=976658\" alt=\"Dashboard Modules Settings\"></a><p>Dashboard Modules Settings</p></li><li><a href=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=1832142\"><img src=\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-7.png?rev=1832142\" alt=\"Dashboard Bot Settings\"></a><p>Dashboard Bot Settings</p></li></ol>\";s:7:\"reviews\";s:16964:\"<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Very Helpful!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/67nj/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2f0cc11605c4e6cc7a6ed6ea330f2574?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/2f0cc11605c4e6cc7a6ed6ea330f2574?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/67nj/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">67nj</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Gennaio 31, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Super handy when it comes to set your layout up in few minutes.<br />I also used it within the super popular Divi theme</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">The plugin i install first when setting a new website</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/skand-snekker/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a47a7f7d1b2fcd6c2ce24f84fb5d32b3?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a47a7f7d1b2fcd6c2ce24f84fb5d32b3?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/skand-snekker/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">Skand Snekker</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Gennaio 14, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">I\'ve been using this plugin since it was wp-maintenance-mode. It\'s nearly the first plugin I install on a new website to begin work. It works as I like weather it is a single site or a multisite. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Of course, resistance to change could have been mitigated by better communication, especially when adding new plugins to the installation... But this plugin really does its job and now we can modify the \"maintenance\" page using Otter or Gutemberg in the back office.<br />It totally matches what I need. Thank you for this plugin!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">installs bloat</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/matrndev/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/cab91ad6cbeb09d2da80b41676e35e45?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/cab91ad6cbeb09d2da80b41676e35e45?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/matrndev/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">matrndev</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Gennaio 4, 2024</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">installs bloat and has unnecessary features, do not recommend.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Is bloated, Installs other crap in your wordpress</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/impressao3d/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/91bf4ff037d69aa13482141e02859f26?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/91bf4ff037d69aa13482141e02859f26?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/impressao3d/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">impressao3d</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Dicembre 20, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">This plugin has installed another plugins on my wordpress without request. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">You know people are not happy about it!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/quantum_leap/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d921655b085c7244c49902d12d292ac8?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/d921655b085c7244c49902d12d292ac8?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/quantum_leap/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">George <small>(quantum_leap)</small></a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Dicembre 13, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Just here to write my experience with this plugin. I am not a person that usually writes reviews but seeing the amount of negative reviews regarding the automatic install of those two plugins and the refusal of the developers to remove that functionality makes me very angry.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">The Optimole plugin installation is a checkbox but from the wording it\'s not very clear that this plugin will be installed automatically. The other plugin, the Otter blocks gets installed automatically because the maintenance page templates make use of that. The installation happened without my knowledge and also messed up my homepage for a second (probably something to do with another block plugin I have installed or a clash with the theme, who knows?). As a result, I don\'t trust this plugin at all, even though I liked the templates. It\'s a matter of principle for me. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">WARNING!!! DON&#039;T INSTALL!!!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/mohaxs/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e70c7d27068469a190f51e02d0edb646?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e70c7d27068469a190f51e02d0edb646?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/mohaxs/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">mohaxs</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Novembre 17, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">I just install the plugin but after that they silently install two another plugin without your permission. Itâs a nightmare. Imagine they also stole your website data. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Trash</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/dado028/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f870216483d14a9882b2f79adbbf54b5?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/f870216483d14a9882b2f79adbbf54b5?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/dado028/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">dado028</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Novembre 10, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">Nightmare... Cant deactivate it , stuck in maintenance mode , and deleted my home page......</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">Installing other plugins without permission....Discraceful!</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"1 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"1\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-empty\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thatfashion/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e135c7e669e3ef86cc6d705c54c09da2?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/e135c7e669e3ef86cc6d705c54c09da2?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/thatfashion/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">SerialDan <small>(thatfashion)</small></a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Novembre 10, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">I\'ve been using Wordpress for years for many different sites covering many different genres, and in all my time I\'ve NEVER had a plugin install unauthorised plugins in the background. How the hell has Wordpress.org allowed this plugin to do this and remain on the marketplace is beyond me. I\'ll me contacing them immediatly to report this plugin.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Issue One, ever since installing It slugged my site to unbearable loading speeds.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Once I came here and seen the issue about it instaling other plugins, I checked and lone and behold it had installed x2 extra plugins without permission.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Quite clearly looking through the plugin data, they sell your data no matter what you agree too.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">PLEASE, people, uninstall this plugin at once and look through your own sites to see what extra plugins have been installed. The dev replied to another comment on this saying it had to do with a pre-designed theme for the maintenance page. A) Why weren\'t we asked about installing this extra plugin for using a pre-designed theme? B) This doesn\'t answer why you would also install an image optimisation plugin without permission?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\"></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">ok</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/petrasova/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/84b824dd2f1216912cb1c5d308c36920?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/84b824dd2f1216912cb1c5d308c36920?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/petrasova/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">petrasova</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Novembre 9, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">vÅ¡e ok</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"review\">\n	<div class=\"review-head\">\n		<div class=\"reviewer-info\">\n			<div class=\"review-title-section\">\n				<h4 class=\"review-title\">So easy to install and use</h4>\n				<div class=\"star-rating\">\n				<div class=\"wporg-ratings\" aria-label=\"5 su 5 stelle\" data-title-template=\"%s su 5 stelle\" data-rating=\"5\" style=\"color:#ffb900;\"><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span><span class=\"star dashicons dashicons-star-filled\"></span></div>				</div>\n			</div>\n			<p class=\"reviewer\">\n				Di <a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/under5tated/\"><img alt=\'\' src=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a2d873d50de9052f9bebf34f1b9b8567?s=16&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g\' srcset=\'https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/a2d873d50de9052f9bebf34f1b9b8567?s=32&#038;d=monsterid&#038;r=g 2x\' class=\'avatar avatar-16 photo\' height=\'16\' width=\'16\' loading=\'lazy\' decoding=\'async\'/></a><a href=\"https://profiles.wordpress.org/under5tated/\" class=\"reviewer-name\">under5tated</a> il <span class=\"review-date\">Ottobre 31, 2023</span>			</p>\n		</div>\n	</div>\n	<div class=\"review-body\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p class=\"\">This took less than 5 minutes to install and setup to take my site off line temporarily. Delighted!!!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n</div>\n\";}s:17:\"short_description\";s:146:\"Easy Drag &amp; Drop Page Builder that adds a splash page to your site that it&#039;s perfect for a coming soon page, maintenance or landing page.\";s:14:\"upgrade_notice\";a:0:{}s:11:\"screenshots\";a:7:{i:1;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:71:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-1.png?rev=976658\";s:7:\"caption\";s:24:\"Maintenance Mode Example\";}i:2;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:71:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-2.png?rev=976658\";s:7:\"caption\";s:27:\"Maintenance Mode Example #2\";}i:3;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:72:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-3.png?rev=1834233\";s:7:\"caption\";s:11:\"Bot Example\";}i:4;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:71:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-4.png?rev=976658\";s:7:\"caption\";s:26:\"Dashboard General Settings\";}i:5;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:71:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-5.png?rev=976658\";s:7:\"caption\";s:25:\"Dashboard Design Settings\";}i:6;a:2:{s:3:\"src\";s:71:\"https://ps.w.org/wp-maintenance-mode/assets/screenshot-6.png?rev=976658\";s:7:\"caption\";s:26:\"Dashboard Mo